{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:Q$objc(cs)NSArray","text":"NSArray<MLNPolygon *>"},{"kind":"text","text":" * "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The area occupied by any interior polygons is excluded from the overall shape."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interior polygons should not overlap. An interior polygon should not have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interior polygons of its own."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If there are no interior polygons, the value of this property is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"]]},"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon(py)interiorPolygons","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"role":"symbol","title":"interiorPolygons"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver."}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon/interiorPolygons":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}],"title":"interiorPolygons"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNPolygon","type":"topic"}}}